ough the long strands at the back and side. Patti stays posed with arms slightly extended, while the girl concentrates, her face close to the doll’s head. The child lifts and smooths sections of hair, showing that the doll’s hair can be handled like a child’s. After grooming, the girl slips her arms around Patti from behind and lifts her. Patti’s body tilts sideways across the girl’s arms, demonstrating the doll’s large size but also that the child can carry her. The girl walks off with the doll held across her chest.\n\nThe scene changes to the floor of the same room. The girl and Patti sit facing one another on a carpet. Patti’s legs are stretched out, and the girl sits with her own legs bent and spread comfortably. Several small toys are scattered near a dresser in the background. The girl handles a dark shoe near Patti’s foot, then leans forward and works at the doll’s shoe and sock as if dressing her. A pair of dark Mary Jane shoes lies between them, and the girl adjusts one at Patti’s foot with both hands.\n\nA bedroom scene follows. Patti lies in a bed under a light-colored blanket or quilt, her head resting on a pillow against a carved wooden headboard. A small bedside table with a lamp sits to the right. The little girl, now beside the bed, lifts the blanket high and pulls it over the doll, then climbs in next to her. The girl nestles under the covers, facing Patti. She smooths and tucks the blanket around them both. Patti’s head remains turned slightly toward the girl, her painted eyes open above the blanket. The child smiles and looks at the doll as if sharing a sleepover. The two lie side by side beneath the covers, the girl animated and happy while Patti’s lifelike face peers calmly out from the bedding.\n\nThe setting then changes to a staged playground with a painted backdrop of trees, clouds, a fence, and a small building labeled “SCHOOL.” The little girl stands near a seesaw. Patti sits on one end of the seesaw, upright, holding the handlebar, her legs extended and her shoes pointed outward. The girl sits or kneels near the other end, interacting with the play equipment as if playing with Patti. More dolls appear around the playground. On the left, a baby-sized doll sits in a sandbox or play area. Another smaller doll sits in a suspended swing with chains. On the right, a larger toddler-like doll stands at the top of a slide platform, wearing a dress and dark shoes, while another doll stands near the ladder. The playground tableau presents several dolls of different sizes posed as playmates.\n\nIndividual members of the Play Pal family are then shown with large white on-screen labels. First, a baby doll sits upright in a play area, one hand raised as if waving. The text across the lower part of the image reads “JOHNNY PLAY PAL” with “3 Months” beneath it. Next, a curly-haired doll sits in a chain swing wearing a light dress. The text reads “SUZY PLAY PAL” with “Age 1” beneath. Then a toddler-sized doll stands on a small platform or at the top of a slide, with curly hair, a short dress, socks, and dark shoes. The text reads “PENNY PLAY PAL” with “Age 2” beneath. Patti appears again in close view, framed against the painted playground background. Her straight hair, bangs, side bow, round cheeks, and smock dress are clearly visible. Bold white text across her reads “PATTI PLAY PAL” with the price “29.95” underneath.\n\nThe final images become more graphic and text-focused. Patti remains faintly visible behind large white lettering as sparkling dots gather around the words. Script text appears and completes the phrase “She’s a wonderful doll.” Below it, more script begins “she’s,” and an oval “IDEAL” logo appears beside it, surrounded by a field of glitter-like stars. The image ends with the “IDEAL” logo enlarged in the center of the screen, white block letters inside a dark oval, against a dark background sprinkled with small star shapes.",
